<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title><%= appInfo.name %> | Cognito SSO Demo</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --shell-bg: <%= theme.shellBackground %>;
            --panel-bg: <%= theme.panelBackground %>;
            --panel-border: <%= theme.panelBorder %>;
            --accent: <%= theme.accent %>;
            --accent-soft: <%= theme.accentSoft %>;
            --text: <%= theme.text %>;
            --muted: <%= theme.muted %>;
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            margin: 0;
            font-family: "Segoe UI", Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            color: var(--text);
            background: var(--shell-bg);
            min-height: 100vh;
        }

        a {
            color: inherit;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .page {
            width: min(1100px, calc(100% - 32px));
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 32px 0 48px;
        }

        .hero {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.46);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
            border-radius: 28px;
            padding: 28px;
            backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
            box-shadow: 0 20px 50px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
        }

        .hero-top {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: space-between;
            gap: 16px;
            align-items: flex-start;
        }

        .hero h1 {
            margin: 12px 0 8px;
            font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.4rem);
            line-height: 1.02;
        }

        .eyebrow {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            background: var(--accent-soft);
            color: var(--accent);
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            font-weight: 700;
            letter-spacing: 0.03em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        .hero p {
            max-width: 700px;
            color: var(--muted);
            font-size: 1rem;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .nav {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 10px;
        }

        .subnav {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 10px;
            margin-top: 18px;
        }

        .nav-link,
        .cta {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            min-height: 44px;
            padding: 0 16px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.74);
            transition: transform 0.18s ease, box-shadow 0.18s ease;
        }

        .nav-link:hover,
        .cta:hover {
            transform: translateY(-1px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
        }

        .nav-link.current {
            background: var(--accent);
            border-color: var(--accent);
            color: white;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .subnav-link {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            min-height: 40px;
            padding: 0 14px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
            color: var(--muted);
        }

        .subnav-link.current {
            background: white;
            color: var(--text);
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .cta.primary {
            background: var(--accent);
            border-color: var(--accent);
            color: white;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .cta.secondary {
            background: transparent;
        }

        .grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
            gap: 18px;
            margin-top: 22px;
        }

        .panel {
            background: var(--panel-bg);
            border: 1px solid var(--panel-border);
            border-radius: 24px;
            padding: 22px;
            box-shadow: 0 14px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
        }

        .panel h2 {
            margin: 0 0 12px;
            font-size: 1.2rem;
        }

        .panel p,
        .panel li {
            color: var(--muted);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .actions {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            gap: 12px;
            margin-top: 18px;
        }

        .kpis {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
            gap: 12px;
            margin-top: 16px;
        }

        .kpi {
            padding: 14px;
            border-radius: 18px;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
            border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
        }

        .kpi strong {
            display: block;
            color: var(--text);
            margin-bottom: 6px;
            font-size: 0.88rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        }

        .mono {
            font-family: Consolas, "Courier New", monospace;
            font-size: 0.95rem;
            color: var(--text);
            word-break: break-word;
        }

        .callout {
            margin-top: 18px;
            padding: 16px 18px;
            border-radius: 18px;
            background: var(--accent-soft);
            border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
        }

        .error {
            margin-top: 16px;
            padding: 16px 18px;
            border-radius: 18px;
            background: #fff0ec;
            border: 1px solid #e7b6a8;
            color: #8a2b12;
        }

        pre {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 18px;
            border-radius: 18px;
            background: #172026;
            color: #f1f5f9;
            overflow: auto;
        }

        ul {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        @media (max-width: 640px) {
            .page {
                width: min(100% - 20px, 1100px);
                padding-top: 20px;
            }

            .hero,
            .panel {
                padding: 18px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="page">
        <section class="hero">
            <div class="hero-top">
                <div>
                    <span class="eyebrow"><%= appInfo.name %> Active</span>
                    <h1>Cognito SSO across App 1 and App 2</h1>
                    <p><%= appInfo.tagline %>. Both apps should use the same Cognito User Pool and Hosted UI domain, but different App Client IDs. After signing in once, open the other app and click Login to see single sign-on in action.</p>
                </div>
                <nav class="nav" aria-label="App switcher">
                    <% navigationApps.forEach((navApp) => { %>
                        <a class="nav-link <%= navApp.isCurrent ? 'current' : '' %>" href="<%= navApp.url %>"><%= navApp.name %></a>
                    <% }) %>
                </nav>
            </div>

            <nav class="subnav" aria-label="Route switcher">
                <% pageLinks.forEach((link) => { %>
                    <a class="subnav-link <%= link.current ? 'current' : '' %>" href="<%= link.href %>"><%= link.label %></a>
                <% }) %>
            </nav>

            <% if (error) { %>
                <div class="error">
                    <strong>Authentication error</strong>
                    <div class="mono"><%= error %></div>
                </div>
            <% } %>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
            <article class="panel">
                <h2>Current App</h2>
                <div class="kpis">
                    <div class="kpi">
                        <strong>Base URL</strong>
                        <div class="mono"><%= appInfo.baseUrl %></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi">
                        <strong>Callback URL</strong>
                        <div class="mono"><%= appInfo.redirectUri %></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi">
                        <strong>App Client ID</strong>
                        <div class="mono"><%= appInfo.clientId %></div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="kpi">
                        <strong>Scopes</strong>
                        <div class="mono"><%= appInfo.scopes %></div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="actions">
                    <% if (isAuthenticated) { %>
                        <a class="cta primary" href="/logout">Logout from <%= appInfo.name %></a>
                    <% } else { %>
                        <a class="cta primary" href="/login">Login with Cognito</a>
                    <% } %>

                    <% otherApps.forEach((otherApp) => { %>
                        <a class="cta secondary" href="<%= otherApp.url %>">Open <%= otherApp.name %></a>
                    <% }) %>
                </div>

                <div class="callout">
                    <% if (isAuthenticated) { %>
                        You already have a local session in <strong><%= appInfo.name %></strong>. Open the other app from the menu and click <strong>Login with Cognito</strong>. Cognito should reuse the Hosted UI session and return immediately.
                    <% } else { %>
                        Start by signing in here. Then switch to the other app from the menu and click <strong>Login with Cognito</strong>. After that, open the protected page in the second app to verify SSO on an authenticated route.
                    <% } %>
                </div>
            </article>

            <article class="panel">
                <h2>What SSO Means Here</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Each Express app keeps its own local session.</li>
                    <li>Cognito Hosted UI keeps the shared login session that enables SSO.</li>
                    <li>Signing in on App 1 does not automatically sign in App 2 until App 2 redirects to Cognito.</li>
                    <li>Once App 2 redirects to Cognito, Cognito can reuse the existing session and return with a new authorization code for App 2.</li>
                    <li>The public page works without login, while the protected page forces the full auth flow.</li>
                </ul>
            </article>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
            <article class="panel">
                <h2>Authentication State</h2>
                <% if (isAuthenticated) { %>
                    <p>The local session for <strong><%= appInfo.name %></strong> is active. These claims came from Cognito:</p>
                    <pre><%= JSON.stringify(userInfo, null, 2) %></pre>
                <% } else { %>
                    <p>No local session is active in this app yet.</p>
                    <p>That is expected before the first login, or after you log out from this app.</p>
                <% } %>
            </article>

            <article class="panel">
                <h2>Suggested Demo Flow</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li>Run <span class="mono">npm run start:app1</span> and <span class="mono">npm run start:app2</span> in separate terminals.</li>
                    <li>Open the public page first to confirm that unauthenticated routes work without Cognito.</li>
                    <li>Open App 1 and click <strong>Login with Cognito</strong>.</li>
                    <li>After you return authenticated, use the top menu to open App 2.</li>
                    <li>In App 2, open the protected page. The app should redirect through Cognito and back.</li>
                    <li>Cognito should reuse the Hosted UI session and send you back without prompting for credentials.</li>
                </ol>
            </article>
        </section>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
